D%5C%22Stock%20photo%20shows%20coast%20of%20Maric%C3%A1%2C%20Brazil.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a8fa4d1a227600e632b9e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222322%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20Maric%C3%A1%2C%20Brazil%2C%20a%20basic%20income%20program%20provides%20financial%20assistance%20to%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%20inhabitants.%3Cp%3Ecaio%20acquesta%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Maric%C3%A1%2C%20Brazil%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.maricabasicincome.com%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520policy%252C%2520known%2520as%2520the%2Cmumbuca%252C%2520a%2520local%2520digital%2520currency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECitizens'%20Basic%20Income%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20provides%20universal%20basic%20income%20to%20over%2093%2C000%20of%20the%20city's%20197%2C000%20residents.%20The%20program%20was%20launched%20in%202019%20to%20revamp%20the%20city's%20basic%20income%20endeavor%20and%20increase%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20recipients%20are%20residents%20of%20Maric%C3%A1%20and%20in%20Brazil's%20federal%20registry%20for%20social%20programs%2C%20which%20identifies%20low-income%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20the%20city%20formed%20the%20Banco%20Mumbuca%20%E2%80%94%20a%20community%20bank%20that%20issues%20a%20digital%20currency%20called%20mumbuca.%20The%20currency%20can%20only%20be%20used%20via%20card%20or%20app%20in%20the%20city%20and%20is%20not%20convertible%20to%20cash.%20Maric%C3%A1%20has%20offered%20some%20residents%20a%20form%20of%20basic%20income%20in%20monthly%20mumbuca%20payments%20since%20then.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20program%20began%20paying%20%2457%20in%20mumbuca%20monthly%20to%20individuals%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0previously%2C%20payments%20were%20made%20to%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Citizens'%20Basic%20Income%20program%20was%20expanded%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20From%20April%202020%20to%20December%202021%2C%20