ew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20gray%20rectangular%20scratching%20post%20is%20placed%20over%20the%20arm%20of%20a%20chair%20to%20protect%20it%20from%20cat%20scratching.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa05e1069331a0011bc6cc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Sofa%20Scratcher%20is%20the%20best%20product%20to%20protecting%20sofas%20and%20chairs%20from%20cat%20scratching.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20shields%20and%20tape%2C%20both%20Sofa%20Scratcher%20models%20have%20a%20rectangular%20polycarbonate%20base%20that%20slips%20under%20the%20leg%20of%20a%20couch%20or%20chair%2C%20using%20the%20furniture's%20weight%20to%20keep%20it%20in%20place.%20Felt%20backing%20on%20the%20scratcher%20prevents%20pilling%20on%20your%20upholstery.%20The%2024-inch-tall%20square%20scratcher%20and%20its%20two%205.5-inch-wide%20panels%20perfectly%20covered%20the%20chair%20and%20couch%20I%20tested%20it%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20taller%20furniture%2C%20you%20may%20need%20scratch%20tape%20or%20a%20furniture%20guard%20to%20protect%20the%20remaining%20inches%20of%20exposed%20furniture.%20Because%20the%20half-moon%20scratcher%20didn't%20match%20the%20shape%20of%20my%20furniture%2C%20it%20left%20gaps%20large%20enough%20for%20a%20determined%20cat%20to%20reach%20the%20upholstery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20furniture%20guard%5C%22%3EBest%20furniture%20guard%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESanchez%20says%20that%20one%20way%20to%20stop%20a%20cat%20from%20scratching%20furniture%20is%20to%20make%20their%20favorite%20scratching%20spots%20less%20desirable.%20Covering%20an%20area%20with%20slick%20vinyl%20can%20discourage%20destructive%20tendencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20two%20vinyl%20guards%20we%20tested%2C%20the%20Clawguard%20Furniture%20Shield%20offered%20the%20most%20protection%20and%20took%20less%20than%20five%20minutes%20to%20install.%20The%20transparent%2C%20flexible%20material%20attaches%20to%20upholstery%20or%20carpeting%20with%20twist%20pins%20inserted%20through%20holes%20that%20run%20the%20length%20of%20the%20shield's%20edges.%20When%20the%20shield%20is%20secured%20tight%2C%20the%20clear%20plastic%20caps%20on%20the%20pins%20look%20like%20small%20buttons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20clear%20plastic%20Clawguard%20Cat%20Furniture%20Shield%20placed%20over%20the%20arm%20of%20an%20upholstered%20chair%20to%20prevent%20damage%20from%20cat%20scratching%20furniture.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa0816469331a0011bc6db5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20best%20furniture%20guard%20is%20easy%20to%20secure%20and%20extra%20durable.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20figuring%20out%20the%20vinyl%20was%20unpleasant%20to%20scratch%20on%20his%20first%20attempt%2C%20my%20furniture-scratching%20cat%20did%20not%20touch%20it%20again%2C%20preferring%20to%20use%20the%20nearby%20posts%20and%20pads%20instead.%20Not%20even%20a%20utility%20knife%20left%20marks%20on%20the%20guard%2C%20and%20a%20pushpin%20could%20only%20fully%20penetrate%20it%20with%20heavy%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20choose%20from%20four%20sizes%2C%20which%20come%20in%20packs%20of%20two.%20You%20can%20also%20cut%20them%20down%20in%20size%20with%20scissors.%20Aside%20from%20how%20well%20they%20protect%20furniture%2C%20the%20best%20thing%20about%20the%20shields%20is%20that%20they%20will%20last%20for%20months%2C%20if%20not%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20made%20of%20clear%20vinyl%2C%20Clawguard%20Furniture%20Shields%20are%20easily%20visible.%20And%20while%20my%20upholstery%20did%20not%20show%20signs%20of%20being%20embedded%20with%20pins%20when%20I%20removed%20the%20guard%20after%20testing%2C%20more%20delicate%20materials%20may.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20scratch%20tape%5C%22%3EBest%20scratch%20tape%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20furniture%20guards%2C%20scratch%20tape%20takes%20the%20fun%20out%20of%20scratching%20a%20couch%20leg%20or%20the%20edge%20of%20a%20carpet.%20Of%20the%20two%20versions%20we%20tested%2C%20we%20found%C2%A0Sticky%20Paws%20was%20best%20at%20deterring%20scratching%20without%20causing%20unnecessary%20fear%2C%20pain%2C%20or%20discomfort.%20This%20tape%20is%20also%20recommended%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgocatgosf.com%2Fabout-dq-go-cat-go%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDaniel%20%26quot%3BDQ%26quot%3B%20Quagliozzi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20cat%20behavior%20consultant%20and%20owner%20of%C2%A0Go%20Cat%20Go!%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESticky%20Paws%20is%20a%20transparent%2C%20double-sided%20tape.%20One%20side%20adheres%20to%20upholstery%2C%20carpeting%2C%20and%20other%20household%20materials%2C%20while%20the%20other%20sticky%20side%20faces%20outward.%20When%20cats%20scratch%2C%20the%20tape%20briefly%20grips%20their%20nails%20and%20paws%2C%20preventing%20them%20from%20digging%20in.%20%26quot%3BSticky%20tape%20is%20not%20too%20aversive%20for%20cats%2C%26quot%3B%20Calder%20says.%20It%20may%20be%20unpleasant%20to%20scratch%2C%20but%20doing%20so%20doesn't%20cause%20discomfort%20or%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESticky%20Paws%20comes%20in%20different%20shapes%20and%20sizes%2C%20but%20our%20favorite%20was%20Sticky%20Paws%20On%20a%20Roll%2C%20which%20works%20like%20a%20packaging%20tape%20dispenser%20so%20you%20can%20easily%20cut%20the%20tape%20to%20size.%20Like%20the%20furniture%20guards%2C%20after%20my%20cat%20got%20his%20paws%20on%20the%20tape%20just%20once%2C%20he%20chose%20not%20to%20focus%20any%20more%20energy%20on%20it%2C%20turning%20instead%20to%20nearby%20posts%20and%20pads.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20package%20of%20sticky%20paws%20XL%20cat%20scratch%20tape%20is%20beside%20a%20roll%20of%20Pioneer%20Sticky%20Paws%20on%20a%20Roll%20cat%20scratch%20tape.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa0867469331a0011bc6dd8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESticky%20Paws%20scratch%20tape%20is%20an%20excellent%20option%20for%20places%20where%20other%20furniture%20protectors%20won't%20fit.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20problem%20with%20using%20Sticky%20Paws%20is%20the%20reason%20it%20works%20in%20the%20first%20place%3A%20Stuff%20sticks%20to%20it.%20Dust%20and%20hair%20collect%20on%20the%20adhesive%20outer%20layer%2C%20although%20I%20was%20surprised%20that%20after%20three%20weeks%20on%20my%20furniture%2C%20it%20had%20collected%20less%20debris%20than%20expected.%20While%20the%20interior%20of%20the%20tape%20adhered%20well%2C%20it's%20more%20temporary%20than%20a%20furniture%20guard%2C%20was%20more%20easily%20penetrated%20in%20our%20testing%2C%20and%20requires%20frequent%20replacement.%20The%20tape%20didn't%20leave%20any%20residue%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20most%20aesthetically%20pleasing%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20nail%20caps%5C%22%3EBest%20nail%20caps%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENail%20caps%20prevent%20your%20cat's%20claws%20from%20scratching%20your%20furniture.%20Calder%20likes%20Soft%20Claws%2C%20and%20out%20of%20the%20two%20nail%20cap%20brands%20we%20considered%2C%20we%20found%20the%20medium-sized%20Soft%20Claws%20nail%20caps%20to%20be%20better%20sized%20for%20a%209-%20to%2013-pound%20cat's%20claws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoft%20Claws%20are%20made%20of%20durable%2C%20flexible%20vinyl%20that%20slips%20over%20the%20nail.%20The%20cat%20claw%20covers%20don't%20interfere%20with%20a%20feline's%20ability%20to%20extend%20or%20retract%20their%20claws%20and%20come%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20colors.%20Super%20strong%2C%20nontoxic%20adhesive%20keeps%20each%20cap%20secure%20for%20four%20to%20six%20weeks.%20Each%20package%20comes%20with%2040%20nail%20caps%2C%20two%20bottles%20of%20adhesive%2C%20and%20six%20applicators.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20package%20of%20Soft%20Claws%20Cat%20Nail%20Caps%20is%20lying%20on%20the%20floor%20beside%20claw%20covers%20and%20nail%20glue.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa177d31df1d5001821885f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20good%20set%20of%20nail%20caps%20can%20protect%20your%20sofa%20against%20damage%20from%20a%20cat's%20claws.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECalder%20and%20Sanchez%20say%20nail%20caps%20can%20be%20a%20good%20solution%20for%20preventing%20damage%20without%20removing%20a%20cat's%20ability%20to%20practice%20the%20innate%20behavior%20of%20scratching.%20While%20it's%20important%20to%20teach%20a%20cat%20to%20focus%20their%20scratching%20on%20posts%20and%20pads%2C%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20%26quot%3Bthese%20nail%20caps%20may%20be%20just%20the%20relief%20your%20furniture%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanchez%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20drawback%20of%20nail%20caps%20is%20that%20many%20cats%2C%20including%20mine%2C%20will%20not%20tolerate%20them.%20Even%20those%20whose%20cats%20are%20okay%20with%20their%20claws%20being%20handled%20may%20find%20getting%20them%20on%20and%20situated%20correctly%20challenging.%20It's%20also%20not%20uncommon%20for%20caps%20to%20fall%20off%20before%20their%20four-%20to%20six-week%20lifespan%20is%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20scratching%20post%5C%22%3EBest%20scratching%20post%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20stop%20your%20cat%20from%20scratching%20furniture%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20not%20to%20punish%20them%20for%20their%20behavior%20but%20to%20redirect%20it.%20Every%20cat%20has%20their%20personal%20scratching%20preference.%20Suppose%20your%20cat%20is%20scratching%20vertically%20on%20your%20furniture.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20they%20will%20likely%20prefer%20a%20vertical%20scratcher%2C%20Quagliozzi%20says.%20If%20they%20scratch%20carpets%20or%20rugs%2C%20a%20horizontal%20scratch%20pad%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20satisfy%20their%20desire.%20Some%2C%20like%20my%20cat%20Osito%2C%20enjoy%20both.%20Whatever%20they%20like%2C%20Calder%20says%20it's%20important%20to%20have%20multiple%20scratchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Skyline%20Sisal%20Cat%20Scratching%20Post%20was%20the%20clear%20favorite%20of%20the%20seven%20vertical%20scratchers%20we%20tested.%20Both%20of%20my%20cats%20returned%20to%20the%20scratcher%20multiple%20times%20a%20day%20during%20the%20first%20month%20of%20testing.%20Six%20months%20later%2C%20one%20still%20scratches%20there%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22On2Pets%20Skyline%20Scratcher%20Post%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61bb4d27260b560019c635c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOur%20experts%20recommend%20a%20high-quality%20scratching%20post%20to%20give%20cats%20an%20appropriate%20spot%20to%20exercise%20their%20instincts.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EResembling%20a%20city%20skyline%2C%20this%20scratcher%20has%20three%20sisal-covered%20vertical%20posts%20at%20heights%20of%2030.5%20inches%2C%2022%20inches%2C%20and%2016.5%20inches%20arranged%20together%20at%20the%20center%20of%20a%20broad%20rectangular%20base.%20The%20base%20is%20covered%20in%20scratchable%20artificial%20turf.%20After%20six%20months%2C%20the%20scratcher's%20sisal%20is%20a%20little%20shaggy%20but%20still%20looks%20nice%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sturdy%20scratcher%20can%20withstand%20up%20to%2032%20pounds%20of%20cat.%20It%20requires%20some%20light%20assembly%20and%20falls%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20pack%20in%20terms%20of%20price.%20Considering%20how%20frequently%20my%20cats%20use%20it%2C%20it's%20well%20worth%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20floor%20scratcher%5C%22%3EBest%20floor%20scratcher%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20cats%20like%20to%20scratch%20vertically%2C%20others%20horizontally%2C%20and%20some%20a%20little%20of%20both.%20If%20you've%20found%20destruction%20on%20rugs%2C%20carpets%2C%20and%20couch%20cushions%2C%20your%20cat%20falls%20into%20one%20of%20the%20latter%20two%20categories%2C%20and%20providing%20them%20with%20a%20properly%20placed%20floor%20scratcher%20may%20solve%20your%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tested%20four%20floor%20scratchers%20and%20found%20the%20simple%20design%20of%20the%20Our%20Pets%20Double-Wide%20Cat%20Scratcher%20was%20the%20most%20universally%20attractive%20to%20our%20feline%20testers.%20This%20affordable%20scratcher%20made%20from%20recycled%20corrugated%20cardboard%20is%2018%20inches%20long%20and%2010%20inches%20wide%20and%20sits%20inside%20a%20cardboard%20frame.%20It%20also%20comes%20with%20a%20small%20bag%20of%20catnip%20to%20help%20entice%20cats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20durable%20interior%20pad%20of%20the%20scratcher%20is%20reversible%2C%20so%20even%20if%20your%20cat%20claws%20through%20the%20top%20layer%2C%20you%20can%20turn%20it%20over.%20How%20long%20that%20will%20take%20is%20specific%20to%20individual%20cats%2C%20but%20ours%20still%20looks%20almost%20new%20after%20nearly%20two%20months%20of%20use%20by%20my%20two%20cats.%20When%20it's%20completely%20worn%20out%2C%20the%20pad%20and%20frame%20can%20be%20recycled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20cat%20cardboard%20scratching%20pad%20is%20inside%20a%20yellow%20and%20white%20box%20on%20the%20floor.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60aea0e5a412370019d322d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20cat%20scratching%20pad%20is%20a%20compact%2C%20budget-friendly%20product%20to%20help%20stop%20your%20cat%20from%20scratching%20furniture.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scratcher%20slides%20around%20a%20bit%20on%20a%20smooth%20floor%20when%20a%20cat%20really%20gets%20clawing%2C%20but%20ours%20has%20never%20flipped%20over%20or%20shot%20across%20the%20room.%20Despite%20the%20sliding%2C%20this%20is%20hands%20down%20my%20timid%20cat's%20favorite%20scratcher.%20She%20uses%20it%20multiple%20times%20daily%20and%20snoozes%20or%20watches%20squirrels%20outside%20the%20window%20while%20on%20the%20pad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20tested%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20tested%20products%20to%20stop%20cats%20from%20scratching%20furniture%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20cat%20reaching%20up%20to%20scratch%20one%20of%20the%20sisal-wrapped%20posts%20on%20the%20On2%20pets%20scratcher.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f64d99d57b7da001ee12772%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOur%20tester%20cats%20loved%20this%20On2Pets%20scratching%20post.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%20products%20were%20provided%20as%20editorial%20review%20samples%20by%20their%20manufacturers%2C%20except%20the%20nail%20caps%2C%20Max%20and%20Marlow%20Tall%20Scratch%20Post%2C%20and%20Furniture%20Defender%20Cat%20Scratching%20Guard%2C%20which%20Business%20Insider%20Reviews%20purchased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20compare%20the%20products%20in%20each%20category%20of%20this%20guide%2C%20I%20devised%20the%20following%20tests%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScratch%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20To%20determine%20how%20the%20furniture%20guards%20and%20scratch%20tape%20would%20hold%20up%20over%20time%2C%20I%20scratched%20them%20with%20three%20different%20tools%3A%20a%20fork%2C%20a%20push%20pin%2C%20and%20an%20X-acto%20knife.%20Each%20tool%20was%20dragged%20across%20the%20same%20section%20of%20the%20product%2050%20consecutive%20times%2C%20and%20I%20noted%20if%20any%20penetrated%20the%20material%20and%20how%20long%20it%20took%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPenetration%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20used%20the%20same%20three%20tools%20in%20the%20penetration%20test.%20I%20conducted%20three%20trials%20with%20each%20tool%20as%20I%20attempted%20to%20make%20a%20hole%20through%20the%20material.%20First%2C%20I%20applied%20light%20pressure%2C%20then%20medium%20pressure%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20my%20full%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENail%20caps%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Because%20neither%20of%20my%20cats%20volunteered%20to%20try%20out%20the%20nail%20caps%2C%20I%20tested%20their%20longevity%20by%20sticking%20two%20caps%20from%20each%20brand%20onto%20the%20tines%20of%20a%20plastic%20fork.%20Each%20week%20over%20five%20weeks%2C%20I%20scraped%20the%20fork%20on%20a%20scratcher%20100%20times%20and%20looked%20for%20any%20shifting%20or%20loosening%20of%20the%20caps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELongevity%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Our%20best%20overall%20product%20and%20top%20scratching%20post%20have%20remained%20in%20use%20since%20testing%20for%20the%20first%20version%20of%20this%20guide%20began%20in%20October%202020.%20I%20assessed%20each%20to%20identify%20any%20aesthetic%20or%20functional%20deterioration%20in%20their%20material%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECat%20attract%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20doused%20each%20floor%20scratcher%20and%20scratching%20post%20with%20catnip%20and%20introduced%20them%20to%20my%20cats.%20I%20placed%20each%20in%20the%20locations%20they%20prefer%20to%20scratch%20and%20rotated%20them%20weekly%2C%20noting%20which%20scratchers%20they%20avoided%2C%20which%20they%20used%20occasionally%2C%20and%20which%20they%20returned%20to%20again%20and%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20stop%20your%20cat%20from%20scratching%20furniture%20FAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3EWhy%20do%20cats%20scratch%20furniture%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EScratching%20is%20a%20natural%20behavior%20for%20cats.%20%26quot%3BScratching%20serves%20many%20functions%20for%20a%20cat%2C%20including%20a%20communication%20tool%20that%20leaves%20both%20scent%20and%20visual%20marks%20at%20a%20site%2C%20a%20way%20to%20clean%20and%20condition%20the%20claw%20beds%2C%20and%20a%20great%20way%20to%20stretch%20the%20muscles%20of%20the%20legs%20and%20toes%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanchez%20says.%20Cats%20who%20don't%20have%20easy%20access%20to%20scratching%20posts%20or%20horizontal%20scratch%20pads%20may%20turn%20their%20claws%20toward%20furniture%20and%20carpeting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20can%20I%20stop%20my%20cat%20from%20scratching%20my%20sofa%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOwning%20a%20scratching%20post%20or%20pad%20isn't%20helpful%20if%20it's%20not%20where%20your%20cat%20likes%20to%20scratch.%20Cats%20need%20a%20variety%20of%20choices%20in%20various%20locations%20to%20be%20fully%20satisfied.%20Sanchez%20recommends%20placing%20them%20in%20high-traffic%20areas%20and%20near%20your%20cat's%20favorite%20resting%20spots.%20The%20material%20a%20scratching%20post%20or%20pad%20is%20made%20from%20may%20also%20determine%20whether%20your%20cat%20prefers%20your%20furniture%20to%20a%20scratching%20post%20or%20pad.%20%26quot%3BSome%20cats%20will%20strictly%20scratch%20on%20softer%20materials%20such%20as%20cardboard%20boxes%20or%20scratch%20pads%2C%20while%20other%20cats%20will%20only%20use%20carpeted%20or%20tall%2C%20sturdy%20posts%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanchez%20says.%20Many%20cats%20enjoy%20scratching%20a%20sisal%20rope%20or%20cloth%2C%20but%20some%20may%20find%20other%20materials%20more%20attractive.%20If%20your%20cat%20is%20attracted%20to%20carpet%2C%20Quagliozzi%20recommends%20framing%20a%20piece%20of%20carpet%20for%20them%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDoes%20cat%20scratching%20deterrent%20spray%20work%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20experts%20say%20that%20cat%20scratching%20deterrent%20sprays%20do%20not%20help%20redirect%20furniture%20scratching.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20really%20work%2C%20and%20they're%20an%20aversive%2C%26quot%3B%20Calder%20says.%20An%20aversive%20is%20any%20tool%20or%20technique%20that%20uses%20discomfort%2C%20pain%2C%20fear%2C%20or%20intimidation%20to%20force%20an%20animal%20to%20change%20their%20behavior.%20Deterrent%20sprays%20are%20aversive%20because%20they%20irritate%20a%20cat's%20acute%20senses%20of%20smell%20and%20taste%2C%20making%20them%20sneeze%20and%20cough.%20Using%20scratch%20tape%20or%20furniture%20guards%20combined%20with%20training%20is%20a%20more%20effective%20long-term%20strategy%20for%20changing%20a%20cat's%20behavior.%20%26quot%3BOur%20goal%20is%20not%20to%20scare%20the%20cat%3B%20it's%20more%20about%20finding%20out%20why%20the%20behavior%20is%20occurring%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Calder%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EShould%20cats%20be%20declawed%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20a%20cat%20from%20scratching%2C%20some%20veterinarians%20offer%20declawing%2C%20a%20surgical%20procedure%20that%20removes%20a%20cat's%20claws.%20Although%20declawing%20techniques%20have%20become%20less%20painful%20with%20laser%20technology%2C%20it's%20a%20surgery%20that%20still%20carries%20potential%20complications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpawproject.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecountries%20and%20US%20cities%20have%20banned%20the%20practice%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20American%20Veterinary%20Medical%20Association%20also%20discourages%20the%20practice%20and%20instead%20recommends%20providing%20scratching%20surfaces%20like%20the%20ones%20featured%20in%20this%20guide%2C%20frequent%20nail%20trims%2C%20and%20positive%20reinforcement%20training.%20Complications%20of%20this%20procedure%20can%20include%20infection%2C%20tissue%20necrosis%2C%20and%20back%20pain%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.humanesociety.org%2Fresources%2Fdeclawing-cats-far-worse-manicure%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHumane%20Society%20of%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20removing%20a%20cat's%20claws%20prevents%20them%20from%20practicing%20innate%20behaviors%20such%20as%20scratching%20and%20climbing.%20Veterinarians%20do%20not%20know%20how%20or%20if%20declawing%20impacts%20a%20cat's%20quality%20of%20life%20and%20psychological%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20cat%20typically%20heals%20from%20laser%20declawing%20in%20around%20three%20weeks%2C%20and%20pain%20can%20be%20managed%20with%20medications%20such%20as%20fentanyl%20patches.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmurtdvm.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Bob%20Murtaugh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20chair%20of%20veterinary%20medicine%20for%20the%20National%20Academies%20of%20Practice%2C%20does%20not%20believe%20the%20procedure%20is%20necessary%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20valid%20medical%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20best%20thing%20is%20to%20just%20provide%20them%20with%20some%20scratching%20opportunities%20and%20to%20train%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Murtaugh%20says.%20%26quot%3BPart%20of%20having%20a%20cat%20recognizing%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20might%20take%20it%20out%20on%20a%20sofa%20every%20once%20in%20a%20while.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20providing%20a%20cat%20with%20acceptable%20scratching%20alternatives%2C%20such%20as%20scratching%20posts%20and%20scratch%20pads%2C%20covering%20a%20cat's%20claws%20with%20nail%20caps%20is%20a%20more%20humane%20option%20than%20removing%20them%20altogether.%C2%A0Murtaugh%20says%20some%20veterinarians%20will%20even%20put%20them%20on%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20overall%3A%20Sofa%20Scratcher%20Squared%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20gray%20rectangular%20scratching%20post%20is%20placed%20over%20the%20arm%20of%20a%20chair%20to%20protect%20it%20from%20cat%20scratching.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa05e1069331a0011bc6cc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Sofa%20Scratcher%20is%20the%20best%20product%20to%20protecting%20sofas%20and%20chairs%20from%20cat%20scratching.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECombination%20scratcher%2Ffurniture%20guard%3B%20fits%20snugly%20against%20a%20couch%2C%20chair%20corner%2C%20or%20furniture%20leg%3B%20held%20in%20place%20by%20weight%20of%20furniture%20instead%20of%20tape%20or%20pins%3B%20available%20in%20five%20colors%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMore%20expensive%20than%20furniture%20guards%20and%20most%20scratching%20posts%2C%20light%20assembly%20required%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20genius%20of%20the%20Sofa%20Scratcher%20Squared%20and%20its%20half-moon-shaped%20cousin%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_090418_best-cat-scratching-products-20%26h%3D00f4a5f5047892caaa28d876a76bb816d196f84b4a304c0bc531a5f9d6c1612a%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f41dbe%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fhow-to-stop-cat-from-scratching-couch%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.chewy.com%252Fsofa-scratcher-furniture-protector%252Fdp%252F243285%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESofa%20Scratcher%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%20is%20that%20its%20sisal-covered%20edges%20fit%20snugly%20against%20a%20couch%20or%20chair.%20This%20provides%20a%20cat%20with%20an%20appropriate%20place%20to%20scratch%20right%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20room%20where%20felines%20prefer%20to%20mark%20their%20territory%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.caldervbs.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChristine%20Calder%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20board-certified%20veterinary%20behaviorist%20at%20Calder%20Veterinary%20Behavior%20Services.%20The%20Sofa%20Scratcher%20lines%20up%20flush%20against%20furniture%2C%20and%20its%20wood%20core%20prevents%20your%20cat%20from%20sinking%20their%20claws%20into%20the%20upholstery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20furniture-scratching%20cat%20seemed%20to%20enjoy%20flexing%20his%20claws%20on%20the%20Sofa%20Scratcher%20Squared%20as%20much%20as%20he%20enjoyed%20using%20them%20on%20my%20couch.%20He%20tore%20at%20the%20sisal%20guard%20every%20time%20he%20jumped%20onto%20the%20furniture%20for%20a%20nap.%20After%20nearly%20six%20months%20of%20use%2C%20it%20still%20looks%20brand%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20shields%20and%20tape%2C%20both%20Sofa%20Scratcher%20models%20have%20a%20rectangular%20polycarbonate%20base%20that%20slips%20under%20the%20leg%20of%20a%20couch%20or%20chair%2C%20using%20the%20furniture's%20weight%20to%20keep%20it%20in%20place.%20Felt%20backing%20on%20the%20scratcher%20prevents%20pilling%20on%20your%20upholstery.%20The%2024-inch-tall%20square%20scratcher%20and%20its%20two%205.5-inch-wide%20panels%20perfectly%20covered%20the%20chair%20and%20couch%20I%20tested%20it%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20taller%20furniture%2C%20you%20may%20need%20scratch%20tape%20or%20a%20furniture%20guard%20to%20protect%20the%20remaining%20inches%20of%20exposed%20furniture.%20Because%20the%20half-moon%20scratcher%20didn't%20match%20the%20shape%20of%20my%20furniture%2C%20it%20left%20gaps%20large%20enough%20for%20a%20determined%20cat%20to%20reach%20the%20upholstery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20furniture%20guard%3A%20Clawguard%20Furniture%20Shields%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20clear%20plastic%20Clawguard%20Cat%20Furniture%20Shield%20placed%20over%20the%20arm%20of%20an%20upholstered%20chair%20to%20prevent%20damage%20from%20cat%20scratching%20furniture.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa0816469331a0011bc6db5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20best%20furniture%20guard%20is%20easy%20to%20secure%20and%20extra%20durable.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETransparent%2C%20flexible%2C%20made%20from%20durable%20marine-grade%20vinyl%2C%20withstands%20sharp%20claws%2C%20easy%20to%20install%20with%20upholstery%20twist%20pins%2C%20waterproof%2C%20comes%20in%20four%20sizes%2C%20can%20be%20cut%20down%20to%20smaller%20sizes%2C%20long-lasting%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EVisible%20on%20furniture%20and%20carpeting%2C%20upholstery%20pins%20may%20leave%20marks%20on%20delicate%20materials%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESanchez%20says%20that%20one%20way%20to%20stop%20a%20cat%20from%20scratching%20furniture%20is%20to%20make%20their%20favorite%20scratching%20spots%20less%20desirable.%20Covering%20an%20area%20with%20slick%20vinyl%20can%20discourage%20destructive%20tendencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20two%20vinyl%20guards%20we%20tested%2C%20the%20Clawguard%20Furniture%20Shield%20offered%20the%20most%20protection%20and%20took%20less%20than%20five%20minutes%20to%20install.%20The%20transparent%2C%20flexible%20material%20attaches%20to%20upholstery%20or%20carpeting%20with%20twist%20pins%20inserted%20through%20holes%20that%20run%20the%20length%20of%20the%20shield's%20edges.%20When%20the%20shield%20is%20secured%20tight%2C%20the%20clear%20plastic%20caps%20on%20the%20pins%20look%20like%20small%20buttons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20figuring%20out%20the%20vinyl%20was%20unpleasant%20to%20scratch%20on%20his%20first%20attempt%2C%20my%20furniture-scratching%20cat%20did%20not%20touch%20it%20again%2C%20preferring%20to%20use%20the%20nearby%20posts%20and%20pads%20instead.%20Not%20even%20a%20utility%20knife%20left%20marks%20on%20the%20guard%2C%20and%20a%20pushpin%20could%20only%20fully%20penetrate%20it%20with%20heavy%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20choose%20from%20four%20sizes%2C%20which%20come%20in%20packs%20of%20two.%20You%20can%20also%20cut%20them%20down%20in%20size%20with%20scissors.%20Aside%20from%20how%20well%20they%20protect%20furniture%2C%20the%20best%20thing%20about%20the%20shields%20is%20that%20they%20will%20last%20for%20months%2C%20if%20not%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20made%20of%20clear%20vinyl%2C%20Clawguard%20Furniture%20Shields%20are%20easily%20visible.%20And%20while%20my%20upholstery%20did%20not%20show%20signs%20of%20being%20embedded%20with%20pins%20when%20I%20removed%20the%20guard%20after%20testing%2C%20more%20delicate%20materials%20may.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20scratch%20tape%3A%20Sticky%20Paws%20on%20a%20Roll%20Furniture%20Strips%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20package%20of%20sticky%20paws%20XL%20cat%20scratch%20tape%20is%20beside%20a%20roll%20of%20Pioneer%20Sticky%20Paws%20on%20a%20Roll%20cat%20scratch%20tape.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa0867469331a0011bc6dd8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESticky%20Paws%20scratch%20tape%20is%20an%20excellent%20option%20for%20places%20where%20other%20furniture%20protectors%20won't%20fit.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAdheres%20to%20a%20variety%20of%20surfaces%2C%20transparent%2C%20comes%20in%20multiple%20sizes%20including%20a%20tape%20roll%2C%20easy%20to%20remove%2C%20doesn't%20leave%20residue%2C%20not%20too%20aversive%20for%20cats%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDebris%20clings%20to%20tape's%20sticky%20exterior%2C%20visible%20on%20furniture%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20furniture%20guards%2C%20scratch%20tape%20takes%20the%20fun%20out%20of%20scratching%20a%20couch%20leg%20or%20the%20edge%20of%20a%20carpet.%20Of%20the%20two%20versions%20we%20tested%2C%20we%20found%C2%A0Sticky%20Paws%20was%20best%20at%20deterring%20scratching%20without%20causing%20unnecessary%20fear%2C%20pain%2C%20or%20discomfort.%20This%20tape%20is%20also%20recommended%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgocatgosf.com%2Fabout-dq-go-cat-go%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDaniel%20%26quot%3BDQ%26quot%3B%20Quagliozzi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20cat%20behavior%20consultant%20and%20owner%20of%C2%A0Go%20Cat%20Go!%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESticky%20Paws%20is%20a%20transparent%2C%20double-sided%20tape.%20One%20side%20adheres%20to%20upholstery%2C%20carpeting%2C%20and%20other%20household%20materials%2C%20while%20the%20other%20sticky%20side%20faces%20outward.%20When%20cats%20scratch%2C%20the%20tape%20briefly%20grips%20their%20nails%20and%20paws%2C%20preventing%20them%20from%20digging%20in.%20%26quot%3BSticky%20tape%20is%20not%20too%20aversive%20for%20cats%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Calder.%20It%20may%20be%20unpleasant%20to%20scratch%2C%20but%20doing%20so%20doesn't%20cause%20discomfort%20or%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESticky%20Paws%20comes%20in%20different%20shapes%20and%20sizes%2C%20but%20our%20favorite%20was%20Sticky%20Paws%20On%20a%20Roll%2C%20which%20works%20like%20a%20packaging%20tape%20dispenser%20so%20you%20can%20easily%20cut%20the%20tape%20to%20size.%20Like%20the%20furniture%20guards%2C%20after%20my%20cat%20got%20his%20paws%20on%20the%20tape%20just%20once%2C%20he%20chose%20not%20to%20focus%20any%20more%20energy%20on%20it%2C%20turning%20instead%20to%20nearby%20posts%20and%20pads.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20problem%20with%20using%20Sticky%20Paws%20is%20the%20reason%20it%20works%20in%20the%20first%20place%3A%20Stuff%20sticks%20to%20it.%20Dust%20and%20hair%20collect%20on%20the%20adhesive%20outer%20layer%2C%20although%20I%20was%20surprised%20that%20after%20three%20weeks%20on%20my%20furniture%2C%20it%20had%20collected%20less%20debris%20than%20expected.%20While%20the%20interior%20of%20the%20tape%20adhered%20well%2C%20it's%20more%20temporary%20than%20a%20furniture%20guard%2C%20was%20more%20easily%20penetrated%20in%20our%20testing%2C%20and%20requires%20frequent%20replacement.%20The%20tape%20didn't%20leave%20any%20residue%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20most%20aesthetically%20pleasing%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20nail%20caps%3A%20Soft%20Claws%20Cat%20Nail%20Caps%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20package%20of%20Soft%20Claws%20Cat%20Nail%20Caps%20is%20lying%20on%20the%20floor%20beside%20claw%20covers%20and%20nail%20glue.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa177d31df1d5001821885f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20good%20set%20of%20nail%20caps%20can%20protect%20your%20sofa%20against%20damage%20from%20a%20cat's%20claws.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFlexible%20vinyl%2C%20fits%20medium-sized%20claws%20well%2C%20variety%20of%20colors%2C%20last%20four%20to%20six%20weeks%2C%20comes%20with%2040%20caps%20plus%20nontoxic%20adhesive%20and%20six%20applicators%2C%20affordable%2C%20doesn't%20interfere%20with%20natural%20scratching%20and%20claw%20extension%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMay%20be%20difficult%20to%20get%20on%2C%20may%20fall%20off%20before%20four%20to%20six%20weeks%20are%20up%2C%20many%20cats%20will%20not%20tolerate%20them%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENail%20caps%20prevent%20your%20cat's%20claws%20from%20scratching%20your%20furniture.%20Calder%20likes%20Soft%20Claws%2C%20and%20out%20of%20the%20two%20nail%20cap%20brands%20we%20considered%2C%20we%20found%20the%20medium-sized%20Soft%20Claws%20nail%20caps%20to%20be%20better%20sized%20for%20a%209-%20to%2013-pound%20cat's%20claws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoft%20Claws%20are%20made%20of%20durable%2C%20flexible%20vinyl%20that%20slips%20over%20the%20nail.%20The%20cat%20claw%20covers%20don't%20interfere%20with%20a%20feline's%20ability%20to%20extend%20or%20retract%20their%20claws%20and%20come%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20colors.%20Super%20strong%2C%20nontoxic%20adhesive%20keeps%20each%20cap%20secure%20for%20four%20to%20six%20weeks.%20Each%20package%20comes%20with%2040%20nail%20caps%2C%20two%20bottles%20of%20adhesive%2C%20and%20six%20applicators.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Calder%20and%20Sanchez%2C%20nail%20caps%20can%20be%20a%20good%20solution%20for%20preventing%20damage%20without%20removing%20a%20cat's%20ability%20to%20practice%20the%20innate%20behavior%20of%20scratching.%20While%20it's%20important%20to%20teach%20a%20cat%20to%20focus%20their%20scratching%20on%20posts%20and%20pads%2C%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20%26quot%3Bthese%20nail%20caps%20may%20be%20just%20the%20relief%20your%20furniture%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sanchez.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20drawback%20of%20nail%20caps%20is%20that%20many%20cats%2C%20including%20mine%2C%20will%20not%20tolerate%20them.%20Even%20those%20whose%20cats%20are%20okay%20with%20their%20claws%20being%20handled%20may%20find%20getting%20them%20on%20and%20situated%20correctly%20challenging.%20It's%20also%20not%20uncommon%20for%20caps%20to%20fall%20off%20before%20their%20four-%20to%20six-week%20lifespan%20is%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20scratching%20post%3A%20On2Pets%20Skyline%20Sisal%20Cat%20Scratching%20Post%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20sisal%20wrapped%20cylinders%20mounted%20on%20a%20green%20faux%20grass%20pad%20as%20a%20cat%20scratching%20post.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa0785991178a0019b3dca0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOur%20experts%20recommend%20a%20high-quality%20scratching%20post%20to%20give%20cats%20an%20appropriate%20spot%20to%20exercise%20their%20instincts.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThree%20scratching%20posts%20of%20different%20heights%2C%20sisal-covered%20posts%2C%20broad%20base%20covered%20in%20scratchable%20artificial%20turf%2C%20holds%20up%20to%2032%20pounds%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERequires%20light%20assembly%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20stop%20your%20cat%20from%20scratching%20furniture%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20not%20to%20punish%20them%20for%20their%20behavior%20but%20to%20redirect%20it.%20Every%20cat%20has%20their%20personal%20scratching%20preference.%20Suppose%20your%20cat%20is%20scratching%20vertically%20on%20your%20furniture.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20they%20will%20likely%20prefer%20a%20vertical%20scratcher%2C%20says%20Quagliozzi.%20If%20they%20scratch%20carpets%20or%20rugs%2C%20a%20horizontal%20scratch%20pad%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20satisfy%20their%20desire.%20Some%2C%20like%20my%20cat%20Osito%2C%20enjoy%20both.%20Whatever%20they%20like%2C%20Calder%20says%20it's%20important%20to%20have%20multiple%20scratchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Skyline%20Sisal%20Cat%20Scratching%20Post%20was%20the%20clear%20favorite%20of%20the%20seven%20vertical%20scratchers%20we%20tested.%20Both%20of%20my%20cats%20returned%20to%20the%20scratcher%20multiple%20times%20a%20day%20during%20the%20first%20month%20of%20testing.%20Six%20months%20later%2C%20one%20still%20scratches%20there%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResembling%20a%20city%20skyline%2C%20this%20scratcher%20has%20three%20sisal-covered%20vertical%20posts%20at%20heights%20of%2030.5%20inches%2C%2022%20inches%2C%20and%2016.5%20inches%20arranged%20together%20at%20the%20center%20of%20a%20broad%20rectangular%20base.%20The%20base%20is%20covered%20in%20scratchable%20artificial%20turf.%20After%20six%20months%2C%20the%20scratcher's%20sisal%20is%20a%20little%20shaggy%20but%20still%20looks%20nice%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sturdy%20scratcher%20can%20withstand%20up%20to%2032%20pounds%20of%20cat.%20It%20requires%20some%20light%20assembly%20and%20falls%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20pack%20in%20terms%20of%20price.%20Considering%20how%20frequently%20my%20cats%20use%20it%2C%20it's%20well%20worth%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20floor%20scratcher%3A%20Our%20Pets%20Double-Wide%20Cat%20Scratcher%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20cat%20cardboard%20scratching%20pad%20is%20inside%20a%20yellow%20and%20white%20box%20on%20the%20floor.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60aea0e5a412370019d322d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20cat%20scratching%20pad%20is%20a%20compact%2C%20budget-friendly%20product%20to%20help%20stop%20your%20cat%20from%20scratching%20furniture.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Simple%20design%2C%20affordable%2C%20made%20from%20recycled%20materials%2C%20recyclable%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESlides%20around%20on%20smooth%20floors%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20cats%20like%20to%20scratch%20vertically%2C%20others%20horizontally%2C%20and%20some%20a%20little%20of%20both.%20If%20you've%20found%20destruction%20on%20rugs%2C%20carpets%2C%20and%20couch%20cushions%2C%20your%20cat%20falls%20into%20one%20of%20the%20latter%20two%20categories%2C%20and%20providing%20them%20with%20a%20properly%20placed%20floor%20scratcher%20may%20solve%20your%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tested%20four%20floor%20scratchers%20and%20found%20the%20simple%20design%20of%20the%20Our%20Pets%20Double-Wide%20Cat%20Scratcher%20was%20the%20most%20universally%20attractive%20to%20our%20feline%20testers.%20This%20affordable%20scratcher%20made%20from%20recycled%20corrugated%20cardboard%20is%2018%20inches%20long%20and%2010%20inches%20wide%20and%20sits%20inside%20a%20cardboard%20frame.%20It%20also%20comes%20with%20a%20small%20bag%20of%20catnip%20to%20help%20entice%20cats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20durable%20interior%20pad%20of%20the%20scratcher%20is%20reversible%2C%20so%20even%20if%20your%20cat%20claws%20through%20the%20top%20layer%2C%20you%20can%20turn%20it%20over.%20How%20long%20that%20will%20take%20is%20specific%20to%20individual%20cats%2C%20but%20ours%20still%20looks%20almost%20new%20after%20nearly%20two%20months%20of%20use%20by%20my%20two%20cats.%20When%20it's%20completely%20worn%20out%2C%20the%20pad%20and%20frame%20can%20be%20recycled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scratcher%20slides%20around%20a%20bit%20on%20a%20smooth%20floor%20when%20a%20cat%20really%20gets%20clawing%2C%20but%20ours%20has%20never%20flipped%20over%20or%20shot%20across%20the%20room.%20Despite%20the%20sliding%2C%20this%20is%20hands%20down%20my%20timid%20cat's%20favorite%20scratcher.%20She%20uses%20it%20multiple%20times%20daily%20and%20snoozes%20or%20watches%20squirrels%20outside%20the%20window%20while%20on%20the%20pad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20tested%20products%20to%20keep%20cats%20from%20scratching%20furniture%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20cat%20reaching%20up%20to%20scratch%20one%20of%20the%20sisal-wrapped%20posts%20on%20the%20On2%20pets%20scratcher.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f64d99d57b7da001ee12772%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOur%20tester%20cats%20loved%20this%20On2Pets%20scratching%20post.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%20products%20were%20provided%20as%20editorial%20review%20samples%20by%20their%20manufacturers%2C%20except%20the%20nail%20caps%2C%20Max%20and%20Marlow%20Tall%20Scratch%20Post%2C%20and%20Furniture%20Defender%20Cat%20Scratching%20Guard%2C%20which%20Insider%20Reviews%20purchased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20objectively%20compare%20the%20products%20in%20each%20category%20of%20this%20guide%2C%20I%20devised%20the%20following%20tests%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScratch%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20To%20determine%20how%20the%20furniture%20guards%20and%20scratch%20tape%20would%20hold%20up%20over%20time%2C%20I%20scratched%20them%20with%20three%20different%20tools%3A%20a%20fork%2C%20a%20push%20pin%2C%20and%20an%20X-acto%20knife.%20Each%20tool%20was%20dragged%20across%20the%20same%20section%20of%20the%20product%2050%20consecutive%20times%2C%20and%20I%20noted%20if%20any%20penetrated%20the%20material%20and%20how%20long%20it%20took%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPenetration%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20used%20the%20same%20three%20tools%20in%20the%20penetration%20test.%20I%20conducted%20three%20trials%20with%20each%20tool%20as%20I%20attempted%20to%20make%20a%20hole%20through%20the%20material.%20First%2C%20I%20applied%20light%20pressure%2C%20then%20medium%20pressure%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20my%20full%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENail%20caps%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Because%20neither%20of%20my%20cats%20volunteered%20to%20try%20out%20the%20nail%20caps%2C%20I%20tested%20their%20longevity%20by%20sticking%20two%20caps%20from%20each%20brand%20onto%20the%20tines%20of%20a%20plastic%20fork.%20Each%20week%20over%20five%20weeks%2C%20I%20scraped%20the%20fork%20on%20a%20scratcher%20100%20times%20and%20looked%20for%20any%20shifting%20or%20loosening%20of%20the%20caps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELongevity%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Our%20best%20overall%20product%20and%20top%20scratching%20post%20have%20remained%20in%20use%20since%20testing%20for%20the%20first%20version%20of%20this%20guide%20began%20in%20October%202020.%20I%20assessed%20each%20to%20identify%20any%20aesthetic%20or%20functional%20deterioration%20in%20their%20material%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECat%20attract%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20doused%20each%20floor%20scratcher%20and%20scratching%20post%20with%20catnip%20and%20introduced%20them%20to%20my%20cats.%20I%20placed%20each%20in%20the%20locations%20they%20prefer%20to%20scratch%20and%20rotated%20them%20weekly%2C%20noting%20which%20scratchers%20they%20avoided%2C%20which%20they%20used%20occasionally%2C%20and%20which%20they%20returned%20to%20again%20and%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20to%20stop%20your%20cat%20from%20scratching%20furniture%20FAQs%3Ch3%3EWhy%20do%20cats%20scratch%20furniture%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EScratching%20is%20a%20natural%20behavior%20for%20cats.%20%26quot%3BScratching%20serves%20many%20functions%20for%20a%20cat%2C%20including%20a%20communication%20tool%20that%20leaves%20both%20scent%20and%20visual%20marks%20at%20a%20site%2C%20a%20way%20to%20clean%20and%20condition%20the%20claw%20beds%2C%20and%20a%20great%20way%20to%20stretch%20the%20muscles%20of%20the%20legs%20and%20toes%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sanchez.%20Cats%20who%20don't%20have%20easy%20access%20to%20scratching%20posts%20or%20horizontal%20scratch%20pads%20may%20turn%20their%20claws%20toward%20furniture%20and%20carpeting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20can%20I%20stop%20my%20cat%20from%20scratching%20my%20sofa%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOwning%20a%20scratching%20post%20or%20pad%20isn't%20helpful%20if%20it's%20not%20where%20your%20cat%20likes%20to%20scratch.%20Cats%20need%20a%20variety%20of%20choices%20in%20various%20locations%20to%20be%20fully%20satisfied.%20Sanchez%20recommends%20placing%20them%20in%20high-traffic%20areas%20and%20near%20your%20cat's%20favorite%20resting%20spots.%20The%20material%20a%20scratching%20post%20or%20pad%20is%20made%20from%20may%20also%20determine%20whether%20your%20cat%20prefers%20your%20furniture%20to%20a%20scratching%20post%20or%20pad.%20%26quot%3BSome%20cats%20will%20strictly%20scratch%20on%20softer%20materials%20such%20as%20cardboard%20boxes%20or%20scratch%20pads%2C%20while%20other%20cats%20will%20only%20use%20carpeted%20or%20tall%2C%20sturdy%20posts%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sanchez.%20Many%20cats%20enjoy%20scratching%20a%20sisal%20rope%20or%20cloth%2C%20but%20some%20may%20find%20other%20materials%20more%20attractive.%20If%20your%20cat%20is%20attracted%20to%20carpet%2C%20Quagliozzi%20recommends%20framing%20a%20piece%20of%20carpet%20for%20them%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDoes%20cat%20scratching%20deterrent%20spray%20work%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20experts%20say%20that%20cat%20scratching%20deterrent%20sprays%20do%20not%20help%20redirect%20furniture%20scratching.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20really%20work%2C%20and%20they're%20an%20aversive%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Calder.%20An%20aversive%20is%20any%20tool%20or%20technique%20that%20uses%20discomfort%2C%20pain%2C%20fear%2C%20or%20intimidation%20to%20force%20an%20animal%20to%20change%20their%20behavior.%20Deterrent%20sprays%20are%20aversive%20because%20they%20irritate%20a%20cat's%20acute%20senses%20of%20smell%20and%20taste%2C%20making%20them%20sneeze%20and%20cough.%20Using%20scratch%20tape%20or%20furniture%20guards%20combined%20with%20training%20is%20a%20more%20effective%20long-term%20strategy%20for%20changing%20a%20cat's%20behavior.%20%26quot%3BOur%20goal%20is%20not%20to%20scare%20the%20cat%3B%20it's%20more%20about%20finding%20out%20why%20the%20behavior%20is%20occurring%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Calder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EShould%20cats%20be%20declawed%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20a%20cat%20from%20scratching%2C%20some%20veterinarians%20offer%20declawing%2C%20a%20surgical%20procedure%20that%20removes%20a%20cat's%20claws.%20Although%20declawing%20techniques%20have%20become%20less%20painful%20with%20laser%20technology%2C%20it's%20a%20surgery%20that%20still%20carries%20potential%20complications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpawproject.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecountries%20and%20US%20cities%20have%20banned%20the%20practice%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20American%20Veterinary%20Medical%20Association%20also%20discourages%20the%20practice%20and%20instead%20recommends%20providing%20scratching%20surfaces%20like%20the%20ones%20featured%20in%20this%20guide%2C%20frequent%20nail%20trims%2C%20and%20positive%20reinforcement%20training.%20Complications%20of%20this%20procedure%20can%20include%20infection%2C%20tissue%20necrosis%2C%20and%20back%20pain%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.humanesociety.org%2Fresources%2Fdeclawing-cats-far-worse-manicure%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHumane%20Society%20of%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20removing%20a%20cat's%20claws%20prevents%20them%20from%20practicing%20innate%20behaviors%20such%20as%20scratching%20and%20climbing.%20Veterinarians%20do%20not%20know%20how%20or%20if%2C%20declawing%20impacts%20a%20cat's%20quality%20of%20life%20and%20psychological%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20cat%20typically%20heals%20from%20laser%20declawing%20in%20around%20three%20weeks%2C%20and%20pain%20can%20be%20managed%20with%20medications%20such%20as%20fentanyl%20patches.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmurtdvm.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBob%20Murtaugh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20chief%20professional%20relations%20officer%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thrivepetcare.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThrive%20Pet%20Healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20does%20not%20believe%20the%20procedure%20is%20necessary%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20valid%20medical%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20best%20thing%20is%20to%20just%20provide%20them%20with%20some%20scratching%20opportunities%20and%20to%20train%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Murtaugh.%20%26quot%3BPart%20of%20having%20a%20cat%20recognizing%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20might%20take%20it%20out%20on%20a%20sofa%20every%20once%20in%20a%20while.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20providing%20a%20cat%20with%20acceptable%20scratching%20alternatives%2C%20such%20as%20scratching%20posts%20and%20scratch%20pads%2C%20covering%20a%20cat's%20claws%20with%20nail%20caps%20is%20a%20more%20humane%20option%20than%20removing%20them%20altogether.%20Some%20veterinarians%20will%20even%20put%20them%20on%20for%20you%2C%20says%20Murtaugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20else%20we%20tested%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20tall%20tan%20scratching%20post%20is%20beside%20a%20shorter%20black%20and%20brown%20scratching%20post%20on%20the%20floor%20in%20front%20of%20a%20fireplace.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fa1833f1df1d500182188b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%20products%20we%20tested%20for%20this%20guide%20to%20protect%20furniture%20from%20cat%20scratching%20are%20high-quality%20enough%20to%20get%20the%20job%20done.%20Here%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20didn't%20quite%20make%20the%20cut%20but%20may%20work%20for%20your%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScratching%20Posts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_090418_best-cat-scratching-products-20%26h%3D97dcf9f62a395d8423cfe04b491ac9c973eb3d83babbec81f9a78c92bddacd95%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f41dbe%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fhow-to-stop-cat-from-scratching-couch%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fgp%252Fproduct%252FB07VNP1326%252Fref%253Das_li_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526tag%253Dbiipgf_11420_cat-scratching-furniture-products-20%2526camp%253D1789%2526creative%253D9325%2526linkCode%253Das2%2526creativeASIN%253DB07VNP1326%2526linkId%253D2c83e3aabe1f65f7129678707f6ab725%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPetfusion%20Ultimate%20Cat%20Window%20Scratching%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20liked%20the%20design%20of%20this%20scratching%20post%2C%20which%20has%20a%20perch%20at%20the%20top%20that%20suctions%20to%20a%20window%20for%