1.%20She%20kept%20her%20expenses%20minimal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20was%20making%20%2430%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20or%20roughly%20%2415%20an%20hour%2C%20she%20refrained%20from%20spending%20on%20anything%20that%20wasn't%20necessary%2C%20like%20clothes%2C%20bags%2C%20or%20eating%20out.%20Every%20time%20she%20wanted%20to%20make%20a%20purchase%2C%20she%20would%20think%20about%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20she%20had%20to%20work%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20it.%20This%20helped%20her%20determine%20whether%20spending%20money%20on%20a%20product%20or%20experience%20was%20worth%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20decided%20to%20live%20with%20her%20parents%20until%20her%20mid-20s%20rather%20than%20move%20to%20the%20city%20like%20many%20of%20her%20friends.%20This%20allowed%20her%20to%20save%20money%20on%20rent.%20She%20bought%20a%20used%20and%20affordable%20car%20so%20she%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20finance%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20many%20people%20don't%20realize%20is%20that%20a%20new%20car%20loses%20value%20as%20soon%20as%20you%20drive%20it%20off%20the%20dealer's%20lot.%20I%20decided%20to%20purchase%20an%20affordable%20but%20safe%20%246%2C700%20used%20car%20with%20all%20cash%20so%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20get%20a%20loan%20on%20a%20depreciating%20asset.%20I%20love%20this%20car%20because%20it%20allowed%20me%20to%20save%20more%20money%20to%20invest%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20worry%20about%20getting%20scratches%20on%20my%20car%2C%26quot%3B%20Tseung%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETseung%20eventually%20moved%20out%20at%2027.%20But%20she%20still%20wanted%20to%20keep%20her%20living%20expenses%20low%2C%20so%20she%20rented%20a%20room%20in%20a%20two-bedroom%20apartment%20with%20two%20other%20roommates.%20The%20living%20room%20was%20turned%20into%20a%20third%20bedroom%20to%20lower%20each%20person's%20rent.%20This%20kept%20Tseung's%20rent%20below%20about%2015%25%20of%20her%20income%2C%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20She%20invests%20in%20opportunities%20that%20can%20generate%20more%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20her%20saving%20habits%2C%20Tseung%20has%20always%20been%20able%20to%20invest%20a%20majority%20of%20her%20money%20into%20things%20that%20generate%20more%20income%2C%20such%20as%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20retirement%20funds%2C%20and%20rental%20properties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20has%20several%20online%20side%20hustles%2C%20including%20affiliate%20marketing%20and%20an%20Etsy%20shop%2C%20and%20she%20spends%20money%20on%20things%20like%20courses%20that%20improve%20her%20skills%2C%20upgrading%20tech%20equipment%2C%20and%20adding%20online%20management%20tools%20to%20run%20her%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20She%20focused%20on%20learning%20high-paying%20skills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETseung%20read%20numerous%20books%2C%20blogs%2C%20and%20watched%20YouTube%20videos%20that%20helped%20her%20change%20her%20mindset%20and%20learn%20the%20technical%20skills%20she%20needed%20to%20take%20on%20jobs%20that%20would%20pay%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20books%20that%20shifted%20how%20she%20thought%20about%20money%2C%20one%20of%20the%20books%20that%20had%20the%20greatest%20impact%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3EThe%204-Hour%20Workweek%3C%2Fspan%3E%26quot%3B%20by%20Timothy%20Ferriss.%20The%20book%20focuses%20on%20escaping%20the%209-to-5%20workweek.%20A%20second%20book%20that%20impacted%20the%20way%20she%20thought%20about%20making%20money%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3ERich%20Dad%20Poor%20Dad%3C%2Fspan%3E%26quot%3B%20by%20Robert%20T.%20Kiyosaki.%20This%20book%20taught%20her%20to%20make%20money%20work%20for%20her%20instead%20of%20working%20for%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20new%20technical%20skills%20she%20was%20learning%2C%20she%20experimented%20by%20implementing%20them%20at%20her%20job%20and%20even%20building%20her%20own%20platforms%20to%20put%20what%20she%20learned%20into%20action.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20definitely%20recommend%20trying%20to%20build%20your%20own%20website%20and%20blog%20because%20you%20learn%20a%20lot%20about%20marketing%20while%20doing%20that%2C%20like%20SEO%2C%20paid%20ads%20with%20social%20media%2C%20copywriting%2C%20and%20things%20like%20that.%20But%20also%20when%20you're%20at%20your%20full-time%20job%2C%20make%20sure%20you're%20taking%20initiative%20with%20new%20projects%20and%20wanting%20to%20learn%20more%20at%20work%20and%20then%20finding%20new%20roles%20that%20will%20push%20you%20to%20not%20just%20do%20the%20same%20thing%20every%20day.%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20great%20way%20to%20grow%20your%20skills%2C%26quot%3B%20Tseung%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20She%20traveled%20the%20world%20for%202%20years%20while%20learning%20to%20generate%20passive%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Tseung%20was%20finally%20able%20to%20spend%20two%20years%20traveling%20the%20world.%20During%20this%20time%2C%20she%20worked%20remotely%2C%20accepting%20three%20part-time%20positions%20that%20allowed%20her%20to%20work%20from%20her%20laptop%20managing