I%20model%20designed%20to%20reason%20more%20like%20humans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eo1%20outperforms%20previous%20models%20in%20complex%20tasks%2C%20especialy%20in%20science%2C%20coding%2C%20and%20math.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20remain%20skeptical%2C%20arguing%20o1%20is%20still%20far%20from%20achieving%20artificial%20general%20intelligence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20line%20separating%20human%20intelligence%20from%20artificial%20intelligence%20just%20got%20more%20narrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20on%20Thursday%20revealed%20o1%2C%20the%20first%20in%20a%20new%20series%20of%20AI%20models%20that%20are%20%26quot%3Bdesigned%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20thinking%20before%20they%20respond%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Findex%2Flearning-to-reason-with-llms%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20model%20can%20work%20through%20complex%20tasks%20and%2C%20in%20comparison%20to%20previous%20models%2C%20solve%20more%20difficult%20problems%20in%20science%2C%20coding%2C%20and%20math.%20In%20essence%2C%20they%20think%20a%20little%20more%20like%20humans%20than%20existing%20AI%20chatbots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20previous%20iterations%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-here-are-the-exams-chatgpt-has-passed-so-far-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20models%20have%20excelled%20on%20standardized%20tests%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20the%20SAT%20to%20the%20Uniform%20Bar%20Examination%2C%20the%20company%20says%20that%20o1%20goes%20a%20step%20further.%20It%20performs%20%26quot%3Bsimilarly%20to%20PhD%20students%20on%20challenging%20benchmark%20tasks%20in%20physics%2C%20chemistry%2C%20and%20biology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20it%20beat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgpt-4o-ai-model-work-easier-for-electricians-plumbers-openai-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGPT%252D4o%252C%2520the%2520company%2527s%2520newest%2Cintelligence%2520of%2520the%2520recent%2520past.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGPT-4o%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20multimodal%20model%20OpenAI%20unveiled%20in%20May%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20qualifying%20exam%20for%20the%20International%20Mathematics%20Olympiad%20by%20a%20long%20shot.%20GPT-4o%20only%20correctly%20solved%2013%25%20of%20the%20exam's%20problems%2C%20while%20o1%20scored%2083%25%2C%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sharp%20surge%20in%20the%20o1's%20reasoning%20capabilities%20comes%2C%20in%20part%2C%20from%20a%20prompting%20technique%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bchain%20of%20thought.%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20said%20o1%20%26quot%3Blearns%20to%20recognize%20and%20correct%20its%20mistakes.%20It%20learns%20to%20break%20down%20tricky%20steps%20into%20simpler%20ones.%20It%20learns%20to%20try%20a%20different%20approach%20when%20the%20current%20one%20isn't%20working.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20there%20aren't%20some%20tradeoffs%20compared%20to%20earlier%20models.%20OpenAI%20noted%20that%20while%20human%20testers%20preferred%20o1's%20responses%20in%20reasoning-heavy%20categories%20like%20data%20analysis%2C%20coding%2C%20and%20math%2C%20GPT-4o%20still%20won%20out%20in%20natural%20language%20tasks%20like%20personal%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20primary%20mission%20has%20long%20been%20to%20create%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agi-artificial-general-intelligence-explained-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20general%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20AGI%2C%20a%20still%20hypothetical%20form%20of%20AI%20that%20mimics%20human%20capabilities.%20Over%20the%20summer%2C%20while%20o1%20was%20still%20in%20development%2C%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-nears-ai-systems-reason-cause-concern-sam-altman-chatgpt-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunveiled%20a%20new%20five-level%20classification%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20tracking%20its%20progress%20toward%20that%20goal.%20Company%20executives%20reportedly%20told%20employees%20that%20o1%20was%20nearing%20a%20level%20two%2C%20which%20it%20identified%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-meta-agi-ai-models-reasoning-race-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Breasoners%26quot%3B%20with%20human-level%20problem-solving%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwharton-mba-professor-requires-students-to-use-chatgpt-ai-cheating-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEthan%20Mollick%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania's%20Wharton%20School%20who%20has%20had%20access%20to%20o1%20for%20over%20a%20month%2C%20said%20the%20model's%20gains%20are%20perhaps%20best%20illustrated%20by%20how%20it%20solves%20crossword%20puzzles.%20Crossword%20puzzles%20are%20typically%20difficult%20for%20large%20language%20models%20to%20solve%20because%20%26quot%3Bthey%20require%20iterative%20solving%3A%20trying%20and%20rejecting%20many%20answers%20that%20all%20affect%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20Mollick%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20on%20his%20Substack.%20Most%20large%20language%20models%20%26quot%3Bcan%20only%20add%20a%20token%2Fword%20at%20a%20time%20to%20their%20answer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20Mollick%20asked%20o1%20to%20solve%20a%20crossword%20puzzle%2C%20it%20thought%20about%20it%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bfull%20108%20seconds%26quot%3B%20before%20responding.%20He%20said%20that%20its%20thoughts%20were%20both%20%26quot%3Billuminating%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20impressive%26quot%3B%20even%20if%20they%20weren't%20fully%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20AI%20experts%2C%20however%2C%20are%20less%20convinced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20Marcus%2C%20a%20New%20York%20University%20professor%20of%20cognitive%20science%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20model%20is%20%26quot%3Bimpressive%20engineering%26quot%3B%20but%20not%20a%20giant%20leap.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20sure%20it%20will%20be%20hyped%20to%20the%20sky%2C%20as%20usual%2C%20but%20it's%20definitely%20not%20close%20to%20AGI%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20OpenAI%20unveiled%20GPT-4%20last%20year%2C%20it's%20been%20releasing%20successive%20iterations%20in%20its%20quest%20to%20invent%20AGI.%20In%20April%2C%20GPT-4%20Turbo%20was%20made%20available%20to%20paid%20subscribers.%20One%20update%20included%20the%20ability%20to%20generate%20responses%20that%20are%20%26quot%3Bmore%20conversational.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20announced%20in%20July%20that%20it's%20testing%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-searchgpt-search-engine-prototype-declares-war-with-google-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20search%20product%20called%20SearchGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20limited%20group%20of%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-new-o1-model-capabilities-agi-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726171262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e34810cfb7f307e571270e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-new-o1-model-capabilities-agi-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OpenAI%20unveiled%20o1%2C%20an%20AI%20model%20designed%20to%20reason%20more%20like%20humans.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40insider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi%2CJyoti%20Mann)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A136%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-new-o1-model-capabilities-agi-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20spent%20nearly%20%243%2C000%20on%20a%20Disney%20vacation.%20I'm%20canceling%20all%20my%20plans%20this%20month%20to%20limit%20my%20spending.%22%2C%22content%22%3